headline: Review Preview: What Shutdown? Stocks Rise.
summary: “Never put off until tomorrow what may be done the day after tomorrow,” Mark Twain so wisely said.  The market seems to have taken heed, delaying any worries about a looming Oct. 1 deadline to fund the federal government.  The S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite added 0.3% and 0.5%, respectively, for their third-highest ever closes.
